 A container of 4,996,200 capsules of Tramadol has been intercepted at the Onne port in Port Harcourt, Rivers State. The capsules weighing 2,498.2kg and packed in 1,387 cartons were intercepted on Tuesday, spokesman of National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) Femi Babafemi said in a statement yesterday. The drugs were spotted upon inspection of a container marked MRKU 0764717 by officials of the NDLEA and Nigeria Customs Service (NCS). Babafemi said the container was on the Agency’s watch list.  He also said one Muntari Hamidu, 42, was arrested  in Nyibango in Jimeta area of  Yola, the Adamawa State capital, with 13 sacks of cannabis sativa weighing 166kg. Another suspect Sani Musa was equally apprehended  with 16.1kg of skunk at Ngurore, Yola South LGA of the state. Both were arrested on Sunday, according to the statement. “On the same day, a team of NDLEA operatives from Ondo State Command also arrested one James Godspower with 36.5kg of cannabis sativa in Faloye, Ogbese, Akure North LGA of Ondo State. “Chairman/Chief Executive of NDLEA, Brig. General Mohamed Buba Marwa (Retd) in his reaction, lauded the renewed synergy between the Agency and other security agencies in its operations.”  